                     <occupation type="ruler">Emperor</occupation>
               <birth when="1399">He was born in <placeName ref="LOC3061Fataga">Faṭagār</placeName></birth>
               <residence><placeName ref="LOC2246DabraB">Dabra Bǝrhan</placeName></residence>
               <floruit when="1434" evidence="internal">He was the fourth son of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName><persName ref="PRS3429DawitII">Dāwit</persName>
                  to become a king and ascended to the throne after several years of chaos following the death of his brother  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS10342Yeshaq">Yǝsḥaq</persName>and 
               the short reigns of another brother King <persName ref="PRS9176TaklaMa">Takla Māryām</persName> in <date>1430-1433</date> as well  as three of his nephews.
                  He was the outstanding ruler of the early Solomonic period, between  <date>1270-1527</date>.  He played a remarkable role for the development of Gǝʿǝz literature </floruit>
                     <death when="1468" evidence="internal"></death>
